Our cheerleaders brought amazing spirit, I loved the majorettes routine she our athletic trainers were top notch. I‚Äôm so very proud of all of our Triad students. Thanks to everyone that joined us tonight in person and online. I am so very thankful for all of the hard work that went into making tonight a success. It was a team effort and everyone came together to help.

I took a few pictures before my phone went dead. Unfortunately it was pretty early in the game when that happened.

Thank you! üòÄüòÄ

post_text:
Today is the day I‚Äôve dreamed about for so long. I‚Äôve been at Triad for 25 months (just over 2 years) and thought about the first home event for our students (football team, cheerleaders, athletic trainers, band, majorettes and track team), staff and community for 24 of those 25 months.

There are still a few things that will be finished in the next month but I just wanted to say thank you!

Thank you for supporting our amazing district and voting yes!

Thank you for trusting me to bring this dream to a reality!

Thank you for supporting every volunteer and contractor that‚Äôs worked so hard to get us to where we are!

Thank you for supporting me!

I‚Äôm more than blessed to be a part of the amazing Triad team and cannot wait to watch many football games, track meets and other events at our new facility.

17 hours until kick off! #cannotwait #greatthingsatTRIAD

post_text:
As we start the first day of school I first have to say that we are all so excited to finally be back. It may not look the way it looked this time last year but we are thankful to have kids back.

We are also excited to release our Portrait of a Graduate. We spent all of last year getting input from parents, community members, students and staff. What is Portrait of a Graduate? It is a set of traits that we want to help students to gain during their PreK-12 time at Triad. We are now working on our Strategic Plan and will work on how we make these traits a priority in every building.

Thanks to everyone that was a part of helping us to create our Portrait of a Graduate. #greatthingatTRIAD

Thank you for all of your patience and understanding in this uncertain time!

post_text: Outstanding Power of the Pen writer Carly Goodman recently received her award from the Better Business Bureau Laws of Life contest. Carly placed 2nd in the Special Theme category-writing her essay on Unity. She received a beautiful acrylic trophy and a check for $75. This was Carly's second year in a row to be recognized for Excellence in Writing by the BBB contest. We are incredibly proud of her! #greatthingsatTRIAD

Triad Junior Football and Cheer camp will be next week! Monday July 27th through July 30th from 6-8 at the elementary school.
Cheer is for grades 3rd-6th. Registration will take place during the camp. We want everyone to know camp is still happening.
The PeeWee board will be meeting this week to discuss our Covid protocol and will release details once they are complete.
